Process: PM-040-040 Develop Supplier Qualification and Certification Processes
</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-E9B52009-3379-4AB8-AB1D-BC05535E57DB" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="18.0" italic="" ref="text-left"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="18.0" italic="" ref="text-right"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Establish procedures for evaluating the supplier's performance, specify qualification as a supplier, and determine procedures and frequency for auditing compliance. This includes procedures which are be used by the company's employees (e.g, inspection criteria, delivery information recorded by receiving personnel) in order to certify vendors, satisfy financial checks (i.e annual reports and credit checks), provide satisfactory responses to a supplier self evaluation (i.e covering quality control, industrial relations history, organization structure, health and safety, etc) and conduct a successful inspection of the supplier premises. Other possible criteria for supplier assessment are : past performance, reputation , visit and appraisal), third party certification, evaluation of sample products.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-364D750A-02A5-4054-863C-742B5D1C5EF0" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="18.0" italic="" ref="text-left"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="18.0" italic="" ref="text-right"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Flow has been migrated to BIC. Please inform the process steward Dhanwantry, Kalyan R &lt;kalyan.r.dhanwantry@intel.com&gt; and BPM Champions D'Elia, Traci &lt;traci.delia@intel.com&gt;,Newman, Jennifer &lt;jennifer.newman@intel.com&gt;of any design changes that occur within the flow moving forward. This will enable us to reflect those changes in the BIC and WIKI business process documentation.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
   </process>
